The Prime Minister will announce that arms export rules are to be streamlined to allow closer military cooperation. He is expected to discuss collaboration in land, sea, air, space and cyber projects. And Mr Johnson is likely to agree UK technical support for new Indian-designed and built fighter jets. The UK will also seek to support India's needs for new technology to identify and respond to threats in the Indian Ocean led by China. Mr Johnson said: "The world faces growing threats from autocratic states which seek to undermine democracy, choke off free and fair trade and trample on sovereignty.The UK's partnership with India is a beacon in these stormy seas. "Our collaboration on the issues that matter, from climate change to energy security and defence, is of vital importance." Mr Johnson will also discuss cooperation on clean energy in his meetings in New Delhi today.